    Data
    Data is the common interface for all Data type classes.
    ElementEntry
    ElementEntry represents an entry of ElementList.
    ElementEntry associates entry's name, data and its data type.

    Code snippet:
    ElementList
    ElementList is a heterogeneous container of complex and primitive data type entries.
    ElementList entries are identified by name.

    FieldEntry
    FieldEntry represents an entry of FieldList.
    FieldList
    FieldList is a heterogeneous container of complex and primitive data type entries.
    FilterEntry
    FilterEntry represents an entry of FilterList.
    FilterList
    FilterList is a heterogeneous container of complex data type entries.
    GenericMsg
    GenericMsg allows applications to bidirectionally send messages without any implied message semantics.
    GenericMsg may be sent on any item stream using OmmConsumer.submit(GenericMsg, long).

    Objects of this class are intended to be short lived or rather transitional.
    This class is designed to efficiently perform setting and getting of information from GenericMsg.
    Objects of this class are not cache-able.
    Decoding of just encoded GenericMsg in the same application is not supported.
    Key
    Key conveys MapEntry key information.
    Map
    Map is a homogeneous container of complex data type entries.
    MapEntry
    MapEntry represents an entry of Map.
    Msg
    Msg interface is for all message representing classes.
    OmmAnsiPage
    OmmAnsiPage represents AnsiPage data format in Omm.
    OmmArray
    OmmArray is a homogeneous container of primitive data type entries.
    OmmArrayEntry
    OmmArrayEntry represents an entry of OmmArray.
    OmmAscii
    OmmAscii represents Ascii string value in Omm.
    OmmBuffer
    OmmBuffer represents a binary buffer value in Omm.
    OmmConsumer
    OmmConsumer class encapsulates functionality of an Omm consuming type application.
    OmmConsumerClient
    OmmConsumerClient class provides callback interfaces to pass received messages.
    OmmConsumerConfig
    OmmConsumerConfig is used to modify configuration and behaviour of OmmConsumer.
    OmmConsumerErrorClient
    OmmConsumerErrorclient class provides callback mechanism used in place of exceptions.
    OmmConsumerEvent
    OmmConsumerEvent encapsulates item identifiers.
    OmmDate

    OmmDateTime

    OmmDouble

    OmmEnum

    OmmError

    OmmFloat
    OmmFloat represents float value in Omm.
    OmmInt

    OmmNiProviderConfig
    OmmNiProviderConfig is used to modify configuration and behavior of OmmProvider

    OmmOpaque
    OmmOpaque represents Opaque data format in Omm.
    OmmProvider
    OmmProvider class encapsulates functionality of an OmmProvider application.

    OmmQos

    OmmReal
    OmmReal represents Real number in Omm.
    OmmRmtes
    OmmRmtes represents Rmtes string value in Omm.
    OmmRmes is a read only class.
    OmmState
    OmmState represents State information in Omm.
    OmmState is used to represent state of item, item group and service.
    OmmTime
    OmmTime represents Time info in Omm.
    OmmTime encapsulates hour, minute, second, millisecond, microsecond and nanosecond information.
    OmmUInt
    OmmUInt represents long value or BigInteger value in Omm.
    OmmUInt is a read only class.
    OmmUtf8
    OmmUtf8 represents Utf8 string value in Omm.
    OmmXml
    OmmXml represents XML data format in Omm.
    Payload
    Payload conveys the data part of item image.
    PostMsg
    PostMsg allows consumer applications to contribute content.
    RefreshMsg
    RefreshMsg conveys item image, state, permission and group information.
    ReqMsg
    ReqMsg allows consumer application to express its interest in an item.
    RmtesBuffer
    RmtesBuffer represents RMTES data.
    RmtesBuffer stores and applies RMTES data.
    Series
    Series is a homogeneous container of complex data type entries.
    Series is a collection which provides iterator over the elements in this collection.
    SeriesEntry
    SeriesEntry represents an entry of Series.
    StatusMsg
    StatusMsg conveys item state information.
    SummaryData
    SummaryData is used to convey Omm SummaryData information optionally present on Map, Series and Vector.
    SummaryData contains objects of complex type.
    TunnelStreamRequest  
    UpdateMsg
    UpdateMsg conveys changes to item data.
    Vector
    Vector is a homogeneous container of complex data type entries.
    Vector is a collection which provides iterator over the elements in this collection.
    Vector entries are identified by index.
    VectorEntry
    VectorEntry represents an entry of Vector.

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    OmmException
    OmmException is a parent class for all exception types thrown by EMA.
    OmmInvalidConfigurationException
    OmmInvalidConfigurationException represents and indicates fatal configuration errors.
    OmmInvalidHandleException
    OmmInvalidHandleException is thrown when application passes in an invalid handle to OmmConsumer.
    OmmInvalidUsageException
    OmmInvalidUsageException is thrown when application violates usage of EMA interfaces.
    OmmOutOfRangeException
    OmmOutOfRangeException is thrown when a passed in method argument is out of range.
    OmmUnsupportedDomainTypeException
    OmmUnsupportedDomainTypeException is thrown when a domain type value is greater than 255.
